```

## 3. Expected output

- Visualize: console prints `[MISSION] Loading default policy from <path>.zip` (replacing the old `[VIZ] Loading model from ...` line) then the pygame window opens and the aircraft flies identically to before — same model, same `deterministic=True` inference, every flight mode (1-8 override keys included) routed through the same single policy.
- If no model file is found: `[MISSION] No default policy loaded — falling back to random actions.` and the env falls back to `action_space.sample()`, same as before.
- Train: zero behavior change — `train.py`/`main.py` weren't touched.

I ran a smoke test in the project venv: `MissionManager(...).load()` loaded `models/latest.zip` successfully, and `get_active_expert(FlightMode.LOITER)` returned the loaded default expert (confirming uniform routing for M1). `visualize.py` compiles cleanly.

